---
import PostLayout from '../layouts/PostLayout.astro';
---

<PostLayout
  title="Привет, мир — sample post"
  description="A hard-coded sample to verify Phase 1 design: prose, language switcher, inline images."
  lang="ru"
  slug="hello-world"
  availableLangs={['ru', 'pt']}
  date="2025-06-08"
  cover="/sample-cover.svg"
>
  <p>
    Это пример абзаца. The article column is capped to ~50em so lines stay comfortable to read at
    any viewport width. Body copy is 1.8rem with a 1.6 line-height.
  </p>

  <h2>A Section Heading</h2>

  <p>Paragraph after an h2. Below is a blockquote — check the left-border and italic treatment:</p>

  <blockquote>
    <p>
      "The most important thing is to make the reader comfortable. Typography is about invisible
      service." — anonymous typographer
    </p>
  </blockquote>

  <p>
    Inline code looks like <code>npm run build</code>. A fenced code block follows:
  </p>

  <pre><code>site: https://blog.umyar.com
output: static
adapter: vercel</code></pre>

  <h3>Inline Image</h3>

  <p>The image below must be full-width-capped, responsive, and rounded:</p>

  <img src="/sample-cover.svg" alt="Gradient sample cover" width="800" height="400" />

  <h3>Lists</h3>

  <ul>
    <li>Montserrat 300 / 400 / 700</li>
    <li>Red→blue gradient on headings</li>
    <li>Black text on white background</li>
  </ul>

  <ol>
    <li>Phase 0 — Scaffold ✓</li>
    <li>Phase 1 — Design system ✓</li>
    <li>Phase 2 — Content model (next)</li>
  </ol>

  <hr />

  <p>
    End of sample. The language switcher above should show <strong>RU</strong> (active, gradient) and
    <strong>PT</strong> (inactive, grey). EN is absent.
  </p>
</PostLayout>
